### Wind Gust: Time-Varying Force

Wind that pulses on and off.

```scheme
(define (update t)
  (letrec
    ((step (lambda (x y vx vy frame)
             (if (> frame 400)
                 '()
                 (let* ((gravity 0.35)
                        (wind (if (and (> frame 80) (< frame 180)) 0.4 0))
                        (drag-x (* -0.02 vx))
                        (drag-y (* -0.02 vy))
                        (total-fx (+ wind drag-x))
                        (total-fy (+ gravity drag-y)))
                   (cons
                     (draw-circle x y 9 \"pink\")
                     (step (+ x vx) (+ y vy)
                           (+ vx total-fx) (+ vy total-fy)
                           (+ frame 1))))))))
    (step 50 50 1.0 0 0)))

(motion 0 400 update)
```

[VISUAL: A pink circle falling and drifting—sudden rightward shove mid-flight, then straight drop again.]

Wind active frames 80–180. Trajectory kinks when wind starts and stops.

