### Angled Bounce: Reflecting Velocity

A ball hitting a wall at an angle—horizontal velocity reverses, vertical unchanged.

```scheme
(define (update t)
  (letrec
    ((step (lambda (x y vx vy frame)
             (if (> frame 400)
                 '()
                 (let* ((gravity 0.4)
                        (wall-x 350)
                        (restitution 0.8)
                        (new-vx (if (and (>= x wall-x) (> vx 0))
                                    (* (- restitution) vx)
                                    vx))
                        (new-x (if (> x wall-x) wall-x x)))
                   (cons
                     (draw-circle new-x y 10 \"blue\")
                     (step (+ new-x new-vx) (+ y vy)
                           new-vx (+ vy gravity)
                           (+ frame 1))))))))
    (step 50 100 2.5 0 0)))

(motion 0 400 update)
```

[VISUAL: A blue circle arcing rightward under gravity, bouncing off a vertical wall, reversing horizontal direction.]

