### Corner Bounce: Two Walls

Ball bouncing inside a box—left and bottom walls.

```scheme
(define (update t)
  (letrec
    ((step (lambda (x y vx vy frame)
             (if (> frame 550)
                 '()
                 (let* ((gravity 0.45)
                        (left 30)
                        (right 370)
                        (bottom 380)
                        (restitution 0.75)
                        (new-vx (cond
                                  ((and (<= x left) (< vx 0)) (* (- restitution) vx))
                                  ((and (>= x right) (> vx 0)) (* (- restitution) vx))
                                  (else vx)))
                        (new-vy (if (and (>= y bottom) (> vy 0))
                                    (* (- restitution) vy)
                                    (+ vy gravity)))
                        (new-x (cond
                                 ((< x left) left)
                                 ((> x right) right)
                                 (else x)))
                        (new-y (if (> y bottom) bottom y)))
                   (cons
                     (draw-circle new-x new-y 10 \"purple\")
                     (step (+ new-x new-vx) (+ new-y new-vy)
                           new-vx new-vy
                           (+ frame 1))))))))
    (step 200 50 1.8 0 0)))

(motion 0 550 update)
```

[VISUAL: A purple circle bouncing inside a bounding box—complex pinball motion.]

Each wall collision flips the appropriate velocity component. Gravity pulls down throughout.

