### Magnetic Attraction Within Range

Force activates only when object enters a radius around the magnet.

```scheme
(define (update t)
  (letrec
    ((step (lambda (x y vx vy frame)
             (if (> frame 400)
                 '()
                 (let* ((mx 300)
                        (my 200)
                        (dx (- mx x))
                        (dy (- my y))
                        (dist (sqrt (+ (* dx dx) (* dy dy))))
                        (gravity 0.3)
                        (in-range? (< dist 120))
                        (mag-strength (if in-range? 0.05 0))
                        (ax (if in-range? (* mag-strength (/ dx dist)) 0))
                        (ay (if in-range? (* mag-strength (/ dy dist)) 0)))
                   (cons
                     (draw-circle x y 9 \"cyan\")
                     (step (+ x vx) (+ y vy)
                           (+ vx ax) (+ vy ay gravity)
                           (+ frame 1))))))))
    (step 80 80 1.5 0.5 0)))

(motion 0 400 update)
```

[VISUAL: A cyan circle falling, then suddenly curving toward a point when it enters an invisible sphere—magnetic capture.]

Magnet at `(300, 200)`. Force zero outside radius 120, strong inside.

