### Rocket Equation: Decreasing Mass

Thrust fixed, but mass decreases (fuel burned)—acceleration grows over time.

*[needs: time-varying mass model in force integration]*

<!-- BUILD: allow parameterizing mass as function of time, recompute acceleration = force / mass each frame -->

```scheme
(define (update t)
  (letrec
    ((step (lambda (y vy mass frame)
             (if (> frame 350)
                 '()
                 (let* ((gravity 0.4)
                        (thrust 8.0)
                        (fuel-rate 0.01)
                        (new-mass (- mass fuel-rate))
                        (accel (/ (- thrust (* gravity mass)) mass)))
                   (cons
                     (draw-circle 200 y 11 \"orange\")
                     (step (+ y vy) (+ vy accel) new-mass (+ frame 1))))))))
    (step 300 0 10.0 0)))

(motion 0 350 update)
```

[VISUAL: An orange circle (rocket) accelerating upward, acceleration increasing as mass drops—exponential velocity gain.]

As `mass` decreases, same `thrust` yields higher `accel`. The rocket speeds up faster late in the burn.

