### Wake Turbulence: Force Behind Moving Object

*[needs: spatial force field modified by entity passage]*

<!-- BUILD: persistent force-field state, entities modifying it over time -->

Proxy: object leaves a trail of attractors.

```scheme
(define (update t)
  (letrec
    ((step (lambda (x y vx vy trail frame)
             (if (> frame 300)
                 '()
                 (let* ((gravity 0.3)
                        (new-trail (if (= (modulo frame 20) 0)
                                       (cons (list x y) trail)
                                       trail))
                        (pull (lambda (tx ty)
                                (let* ((dx (- tx x)) (dy (- ty y))
                                       (dist (sqrt (+ (* dx dx) (* dy dy)))))
                                  (if (< dist 50)
                                      (list (* 0.01 (/ dx dist)) (* 0.01 (/ dy dist)))
                                      (list 0 0)))))
                        (forces (map (lambda (p) (pull (car p) (cadr p))) new-trail))
                        (sum-fx (apply + (map car forces)))
                        (sum-fy (apply + (map cadr forces))))
                   (cons
                     (draw-circle x y 8 \"purple\")
                     (step (+ x vx) (+ y vy)
                           (+ vx sum-fx) (+ vy sum-fy gravity)
                           new-trail (+ frame 1))))))))
    (step 50 100 2.0 0 '() 0)))

(motion 0 300 update)
```

*[needs: map/apply over lists in motion context]*

<!-- BUILD: list comprehensions or iterative accumulators in integrator -->

[VISUAL: A purple circle moving rightward, leaving attractors that tug on it—wavy, self-interacting path.]

Each dropped point pulls nearby object—creates wake effect.

